    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-07-02T18:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-07-02T18:45:00-05:00" n="336"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d336">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/372: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-07-02T18:00:00-05:45"
                            >July 2, 1930—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>80. Department’s 54, June 19, 7 p.m. The draft protocol of agreement transcribed
                    in Department’s mail instruction No. 16 of May 21<note n="88" xml:id="d336fn88"
                        >See footnote 84, <ref target="#pg_361">p. 361</ref>.</note> was submitted
                    to the Nicaraguan Government today.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tegucigalpa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
